1. Check the current changes in feature branch:
    git status
2. Track current changes:
    git add -A 
3. Stash local changes:
    git stash
4. Switch to master branch:
    git checkout master
5. Pull the latest changes from remote master branch:
    git pull --rebase
6. Switch back to the feature branch:
    git checkout featureBranckName
7. Merge master into feature branch:
    git merge master
8. Get local changes back from stash:
    git stash pop
    
--------------------Resolve the conflicts if there are any-------

9. Check the changes again
    git status
10. Add the current changes:
    git add -A
11. Commit all the changes:
    git commit -m   "commit message"
12. Push changes to remote feature branch:
    git push

